external_knowledge:
- "Most recent performance metrics" refers to the latest data collection date for each well;
- "Performance metrics" include barrels of oil per day (bopd), barrels of water per day (bwpd), and million standard cubic feet of gas per day (mmscfd);
- "Location" includes the location name, city, state, and country of the well;
- "Type" includes the type name and sub-type of the well.

- 'Top producers' refers to wells with the highest total production;
- Total production is the sum of barrels of oil per day (bopd), barrels of water per day (bwpd), and million standard cubic feet of gas per day (mmscfd);
- The query returns the top 5 wells based on total production.

- 'Guardians of the well group's secrets' refers to the operators who have accessed the performance data of the well group;
- 'Unveil them' refers to the date and time when the performance data was accessed;
- 'What did they do' refers to the type of access (e.g., view, download);
- 'How long did they linger' refers to the duration of access in minutes.

- An "active alert" is an ongoing issue that requires attention;
- A "resolved alert" is an issue that has been addressed and closed;
- The "operator" is the user responsible for the well.

- "prodigious producers" refers to wells with an average production rate greater than 500 barrels of oil per day;
- "vast oil fields" is a metaphorical expression used to describe the extensive area where oil wells are located;
- "types of wells" refers to the different categories or classifications of oil wells.

- "Limited flow" refers to wells with a production rate of less than 100 barrels of oil per day;
- "Visited more than five times" means the well has been accessed more than 5 times;
- " Maintain a certain level of production" refers to the average barrels of oil produced per day (bopd);
- "Los Angeles" is the city where the wells are located.

- 'Active' wells are those that are currently operational and in use;
- 'Download' in the context of access events refers to the action of retrieving data or files from the well;
- The date range '2023-05-01' to '2023-05-31' specifies the month of May 2023.

- "whispers of alerts" refers to the different types of alerts (e.g., high pressure, low production) that occur at the wells;
- "strength of their voice" refers to the count of alerts (`alert_count`);
- "locale" refers to the `location_name` in the `locations` table.

- "average daily production" is calculated as the average of barrels of oil, water, and gas produced per day;
- "top 5 wells" are determined by ranking the wells based on their average daily production in descending order;
- "access count" refers to the total number of access events logged for the well.

- Active alerts are currently unresolved and ongoing;
- High-pressure alerts indicate that the well is experiencing pressures above safe operating levels;
- Performance metrics include barrels of oil per day (bopd), barrels of water per day (bwpd), million standard cubic feet of gas per day (mmscfd), and an unknown performance metric (x).

- "latest performance metrics" refers to the most recent data collected for each well;
- "location details" include the location name, city, state, and country;
- "type details" include the type name and sub-type of the well.

- "latest performance report" refers to the most recent data collection date for each well;
- "location" is a combination of the city and state where the well is situated;
- "oil production" is measured in barrels of oil per day (bopd);
- "water production" is measured in barrels of water per day (bwpd);
- "gas production" is measured in million standard cubic feet of gas per day (mmscfd);
- "well status" indicates the current operational state of the well.
